WEBVTT

00:03.120 --> 00:07.400
This programme
contains strong language

00:07.400 --> 00:13.520
CHANTING: Genesis. Genesis.
Genesis. Genesis...

00:16.239 --> 00:19.360
CHANTING CONTINUES

00:26.880 --> 00:29.320
MUSIC: Turn It On Again

00:34.280 --> 00:36.440
Yeah, forget about all this
other bullshit.

00:36.440 --> 00:37.840
We are entertaining people,

00:37.840 --> 00:41.520
and if they're entertained
we've done our job properly!

00:41.520 --> 00:43.160
MUSIC: Invisible Touch

00:43.160 --> 00:45.600
# She seems to have an
invisible touch yeah

00:45.600 --> 00:48.720
# She reaches in and she grabs right
hold of your heart... #

00:48.720 --> 00:50.880
No, I love this.
It's great having hits.

00:50.880 --> 00:52.680
MUSIC: Jesus He Knows Me

00:52.680 --> 00:55.840
# Cos Jesus he knows me
and he knows I'm right... #

00:55.840 --> 00:58.840
In those days there were no real
rules. I think

00:58.840 --> 01:00.800
we were just trying to be
a bit different,

01:00.800 --> 01:03.200
because the canvas
in those days in the '60s

01:03.200 --> 01:04.879
and the '70s was pretty blank.

01:04.879 --> 01:07.280
MUSIC: The Knife

01:07.280 --> 01:09.680
# Carry their heads
to the palace of old

01:09.680 --> 01:11.760
# Hang them high
let the blood flow... #

01:13.280 --> 01:15.240
The basic feel was radically
different

01:15.240 --> 01:16.680
than anything I'd ever done.

01:16.680 --> 01:18.680
Very British, actually!

01:20.400 --> 01:22.560
Aye, aye, aye, ah!

01:22.560 --> 01:25.800
It's not country, it's not rock,
it's not jazz, you know,

01:25.800 --> 01:27.360
it's Genesis.

01:27.360 --> 01:31.600
# There must be
some misunderstanding... #

01:33.120 --> 01:36.320
A very competitive band,
no doubt about that. Very gifted,

01:36.320 --> 01:39.400
but with those gifts,
you know, there's a certain price.

01:39.400 --> 01:41.320
MUSIC: I Can't Dance

01:41.320 --> 01:44.480
It was always, you know,
beating each other into submission.

01:44.480 --> 01:46.600
# I can't talk... #

01:46.600 --> 01:47.720
We pulled rank!

01:47.720 --> 01:51.400
# The only thing about me is the way
that I walk... #

01:51.400 --> 01:54.240
Peter and I used to fight a lot.
Very close friends but, you know,

01:54.240 --> 01:56.960
used to argue about silly
little things.

01:56.960 --> 02:00.160
MUSIC: I Know What I Like
(In Your Wardrobe)

02:00.160 --> 02:03.800
No, he was a really awkward bastard!

02:03.800 --> 02:05.600
But we loved each other too,

02:05.600 --> 02:07.840
you know, there was a real bond.

02:07.840 --> 02:11.120
They were at the forefront of what
we now think of as prog rock.

02:11.120 --> 02:13.240
Then in the '80s,
they were a massive

02:13.240 --> 02:15.800
rock/pop band on both
sides of the Atlantic.

02:15.800 --> 02:17.680
MUSIC: That's All

02:17.680 --> 02:19.480
# Just as I thought
it was going all right

02:19.480 --> 02:21.480
# I found that I'm wrong
when I thought I was right

02:21.480 --> 02:24.080
# It's always the same
it's just a shame

02:24.080 --> 02:25.920
# That's all... #

02:25.920 --> 02:29.160
Genesis were never cool, and Genesis
are proof that, ultimately,

02:29.160 --> 02:30.880
in rock music brains win out.

02:30.880 --> 02:32.480
MUSIC: Sledgehammer by Peter Gabriel

02:32.480 --> 02:37.280
# I wanna be your sledgehammer... #

02:37.280 --> 02:41.760
There's something in the DNA of that
group that's still connected,

02:41.760 --> 02:44.080
even though they were
in different places.

02:44.080 --> 02:46.640
MUSIC: In The Air Tonight
by Phil Collins

02:46.640 --> 02:51.400
# I can feel it
coming in the air tonight... #

02:51.400 --> 02:54.760
Whenever, sort of, Spinal Tap
is on or something and you see these

02:54.760 --> 03:00.360
moments you think, "I've been in a
band like that! That's Genesis".

03:00.360 --> 03:01.640
No, they don't think so.

03:09.400 --> 03:12.960
We had something that none of us
could do on our own.

